Previous Work
The Space Integrated GPS/INS (SIGI) is an example of a spaceborne integrated GPS/INS system.3 SIGI is used on the ISS and was planned to be used on the Crew Return Vehicle (CRV). However, it is not known whether SIGI will meet the navigation requirements for all ﬂight phases or whether it will meet the size, weight, and power requirements for the next generation RLV. In addition, the GPS and INS in SIGI are integrated in a loosely coupled architecture so it may be possible to improve its navigation performance by changing to a more tightly integrated design.
Much work has been done on integrated GPS/INS systems for aircraft and missiles. There are many examples of these systems in operation today, such as the Honeywell H764G Embedded GPS/INS, which is currently being ﬂown in several military aircraft and

