The major sources of error in an INS include initialization errors, system alignment errors, sensor errors, gravity model errors and quantization and computational errors. These errors are characterized in the INS error model.
The gyros and accelerometers are ﬁxed to the body of the vehicle in a strapdown INS. Therefore, the outputs of the accelerometers and gyros are assumed to be provided in the body frame with small misalignments as described in the INS error model.

