GPS Measurement Model
A model of the measurements obtained by a GPS receiver operating in the vicinity of the ISS is needed to quantify GPS navigation performance. The GPS measurement model includes a model of the GPS constellation, a range measurement error model, a GPS signal blockage model and a multipath model.

GPS Constellation Model
A model of the GPS constellation was constructed from a daily global broadcast ephemeris ﬁle in RINEX format from the National Geodetic Survey CORS data website. This ﬁle contains the GPS broadcast ephemeris parameters for each satellite in the constellation for March 1, 2001. There were a total of 29 satellites in the constellation. The ephemeris parameters and the equations used to determine the positions of the GPS satellites at a given time are described in GPS-ICD-200.10 This GPS constellation model was used for all simulations in this study.

