The ISS multipath model computes the errors due to multipath in GPS carrier phase measurements only. The capability to compute the errors in GPS code measurements will be incorporated in the future. Therefore, the ISS multipath model is not used in the rest of this study but is included to present the current status of this work.
In formulating this model, the following assumptions are made:
1. If a GPS signal is not blocked by the ISS, it is subject to multipath.
2. For each GPS signal that is not blocked by the ISS, many reﬂections are caused and there is no dominant reﬂector.
3. The phases of the reﬂections are uniformly distributed over [0, 2π). The rationale for this assumption is explained later in the paper.
4. The relative velocity between the chaser spacecraft and ISS is small so that there is no relative Doppler eﬀect between the direct and reﬂected signals.
