Results
A simulation of the GPS/INS extended Kalman ﬁlter described in the preceding sections was developed. Three test cases were run. During test cases 1 and 2, the spacecraft was in an unperturbed two-body orbit with orbit elements given in Table 1 and the ISS blockage and multipath models were not used. Test case 1 was a nominal ﬁlter run where GPS measurements are continually fed into the ﬁlter. In test case 2, GPS measurements were completely blocked out for a period of 600 seconds. In test case 3, the spacecraft was started on a trajectory designed to achieve rendezvous with the ISS in one orbit period. The ISS blockage model was included in test case 3 to illustrate the eﬀects of GPS signal blockage by the ISS on ﬁlter performance.
In all test cases, the parameters presented in Table 4 were used to simulate the gyros and accelerometers of the SIGI.6
