Conclusions
Error models for INS and GPS navigation sensors operating in the vicinity of the ISS have been developed. The GPS error model includes the eﬀects of GPS signal blockage and multipath in the vicinity of the ISS. These error models have been used to form an integrated GPS/INS EKF. A simulation of the ﬁlter has been developed and the ﬁrst test case shows position errors of less than 1 meter and velocity errors of less than 0.02 m/s in each axis. The second test case shows the position errors grow to approximately 47.5 meters and the velocity errors grow to 0.13 m/s

